metadata.name: AutomataPunk, The Masquerader #361
metadata.description:
A playful spin on PFPs, and the prevalence of them on social media, especially among the NFT community.
The characters are procedurally generated, and then colored and texturized using 1D Cellular Automata.
Masqueraders hide their rarity scores. The cutest or most unusual one will be the most popular.
Their dimensions are always a multiple of 360.

Controls:
- Press 's' to save a PNG file.
- Press 't' to toggle, for a larger and higher resolution version that once complete can be saved as a 3600x3600 PNG by pressing 's'. In this mode, the Masquerader may become much larger than your screen. Wait for its render to complete before saving it. Toggle back to the regular size by pressing 't' again.

License:
See included LICENSE.md

Credits:
Made in p5js

metadata.name: Dazzle Bloom #10
metadata.description:
The second ‘Dazzle’ work, takes the sharp angles and stark colours of warship camouflage and places it inside a scattering of petals.  Contradicting their purpose through nature, life and creation.

There will always be a red bloom on the pattern, sometimes that’s all that will be visible. While it's possible that two or more may appear, I have yet to witness such a display. 

A ship's cat may also make a rare appearance.

The knocked-back dazzle pattern is crisscrossed with dazzle vines, to feature more in my next dazzle work, these are the life of the plant and a network in action.

The petals may be overlaid with colourful blooms altering the energy of the piece.
 
Finally pressing ‘s’ in open view will download a 3000x3000 printable png which looks spectacular printed at 12x12.
The work takes a few seconds to render – anticipation!

Enjoy your visit to the Dazzle Blooms.

metadata.name: Reveries Automata #26
metadata.description:
"The lifetime of a being translated into dualistic combinations. Each individual maintains their perspective of things. Each individual has its pillars and its interferences. A life without concerns can be cleaner and quieter, but undeniably a little chaos can add to the beauty of a whole. It's all about it. Order. Chaos. Singularity is precious. Differences are our riches. Royal beings."

"Reveries Automata" is a generative project that combines AI Art with creative coding. This project was made to be minted on Fxhash and it's inspired on my previous collection "Reveries" where I explore the abstract nuances of art using diffusion models.

I wanted to explore this field of image composition inside creative coding. The solution I came up with was to reveal the images using coded masks.
There are 3 main functions for that:

The Pillars - made basically tiling a separate layer proportionally in the canvas with random sizes, position and rotation (just 2 options for this one, 0 or 90 degrees). Then using this layer as a mask to my base image. Tinted in the colors white, black, blue, red, gold or green.

The Splashes -  A function that makes random ellipses around the canvas in a separate layer, attached in the back and front pillar. And, again, using this layer as a mask to my base image. Tinted in the same color the pillar received.

The Interferences - Probably the one that gave me more trouble to adapt. This funcion is a flow field that uses the color and brightness of my base image to draw and color itself. First I plot particles to use as initial position of the flow and make them draw based on the difference in brightness of my base image. The flow is coloured getting the pixel position of that base image. Tinted in the colors white, gold or black.

To support those code functions and to make sure that the outputs will have many variations, I've prompted and composited 40 base images that are used as background, patterns, textures, flow drawing/colouring and frames.

There are concrete textures, painting flow textures and golden foil textures for background and pillars; Rough contrasted painting flows (white and gold) for the interferences; Labyrinth, Rectangular and Copacabana patterns; 6 paper frames variations to finalize the composition.

Press "G" to save currebt .png canvas.

Read more about: https://brunomerli.com/reveries-automata

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Lucky Oracles #120
metadata.description:
"Lucky Oracles" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

Eko33, is a Swiss-French generative artist who has been at the forefront of digital arts since 1999 when he started writing code to create generative artworks and installations. He made his debut using a Commodore SX-64 and floppy disks. Since then, his work has been exhibited in Museums, International art fairs, and biennales. His work is focused on nonfigurative, generative art while using custom algorithms and innovative technology.

Official Website: https://www.eko33.com/ Official Twitter account: https://twitter.com/eko3316 Official Instagram account: https://www.instagram.com/eko33studio/ https://linktr.ee/eko33 "I create deterministic generative art based on crypto hash seeds. Maximizing algorithmic diversity."

If you want to receive an e-mail alert when I release new artwork subscribe here => https://eko33.com/email-alerts

metadata.name: Flow #433
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022
